library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)

burgers <- data.frame(employee=c("Bob", "Gene",
                              "Linda", "Louise",
                              "Tina"),
                   time=c(25, 30, 60, 20, 50),
                   age=c(42, 11, 39, 9, 13),
                   interest=c("cooking", "music", "wine", "chaos", "horses"))

burgers

burgers <- burgers %>% 
  mutate(where="front")

burgers
ggplot(burgers, aes(x=where, y=time, fill=employee)) + 
  geom_col(position="stack")
